    "In the current era characterized by significant technological advancements, it is noteworthy that farmers continue to follow traditional practices regarding disease identification in crops.",
    "Rather than depend on modern specialized tools, farmers persist in personally and visually examining the crops to detect any signs of disease (Ayoub Shaikh et al, 2022).",
    "The traditional methods of visually inspecting and evaluating crops solely based on the farmer's expertise present several challenges and limitations in agricultural research.",
    "In the worst-case scenario, an undetected crop infection might cause the entire crop to decline, hurting yield.",
    "Certain agricultural diseases may exhibit inconspicuous symptoms, posing challenges in determining the appropriate way of action."
